    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The arrangement of works in an installation or display as a specifically spaced sequence of points which the viewer is intended to follow, pausing at each work. An example is the traditional stations of the cross, although the term is most often used for contemporary art installations.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
